## Shared Test Helper (top of `client.test.js`)

Define this helper **once at the top of the test file** and use it for **every** mock response throughout all subtasks. This is required because after subtask 3 `apiFetch` always calls `response.headers.get('content-length')` — mocks lacking a `headers` object will throw `TypeError` when the full suite runs.

```js
function mockResponse(body, { status = 200, headers = {} } = {}) {
  return {
    ok: status >= 200 && status < 300,
    status,
    json: () => Promise.resolve(body),
    headers: { get: (name) => headers[name.toLowerCase()] ?? null },
  };
}
```

Usage: `vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(mockResponse([]))` — always pass through `mockResponse`, never a raw object literal.

